<subSubSection pageNumber="469" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="469">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="469">Note:</emphasis>
See Foggi &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="469">Taxon</emphasis>
50: 1101. 2002) for a review of the application of this name. Their acceptance of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rauschertâ€™s">Rauschert's</normalizedToken>
choice of 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
(and their own epitypification) fixes the application of the name to the plant of dry grasslands (also known as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jacq.) Wettst." authorityName="Lassen" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sesleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="varia">
